                <note rend="inline" type="source">819.415C/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">South</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-04-24T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1926—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. Your despatch No. 678, April 2, 1925. Department assumes congress to which
                    invitation refers will be of a purely ceremonial and commemorative nature and
                    that no discussion of international matters is contemplated. Discreetly verify
                    and report by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
